About the Rating Systems

GamerPowerLevel(tm) - WHR (Primary)

  • Algorithm: Whole History Rating (WHR) - considers your entire match history to compute skill
  • Key Feature: Retroactively updates past ratings as new data comes in, giving a more accurate picture of skill over time
  • Ranking: Players are ranked by WHR as the primary metric
  • Confidence: Lower uncertainty = more reliable rating

TrueGamerRatingPointz(tm) - Glicko-2 (Secondary)

  • Algorithm: Glicko-2 - processes matches chronologically with rating deviation and volatility
  • Key Feature: Good for tracking rating changes over time, accounts for periods of inactivity
  • Starting Rating: All players start at 1500

General Rules

  • 1v1 Only: Team events (2v2, doubles) are excluded from rating calculations
  • Minimum Matches: Players need at least 3 non-DQ matches to be ranked
  • DQ Matches: Disqualification matches are excluded from all rating calculations
